Code Development Guidelines:

Language Requirement: All code and comments must be written in English only.
Pre-coding Review: Before writing any new code, always review the entire existing architecture and codebase structure.
Consistency Requirement: When adding new code, the framework and structure must follow and reference the existing coding style and patterns.
Style Adherence: Maintain consistency with established conventions including:

Naming conventions
Code organization patterns
Comment formatting
Function/class structure
Error handling approaches


Please ensure all code contributions align with these guidelines to maintain codebase coherence and readability.